data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** Both work without needing `unsafe` — you can write:

```csharp
Span<nint>  nints  = stackalloc nint[5];
Span<nuint> nuints = stackalloc nuint[3];
```

On this 64-bit runtime, `nint`/`nuint` are 8 bytes each. The only caveat is that `sizeof(nint)` requires an `unsafe` context (use `nint.Size` instead).
